  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 51 vocab + 28 grammar (one structure: have to / don't have to, 11 formats). No grants needed for the structure (have/has/to/don't/doesn't are function words); granted left/right for the unit's position vocab (left-hand/middle/right-hand). This unit drove two systemic refinements (committed): V-8 HEADWORD_GLUE now includes pronouns (so \"poor you\"'s def isn't flagged for \"you\"), and the matcher's unknownTokens now does greedy phrase-match BEFORE the granted-single shortcut (granting \"left\" no longer orphaned \"hand\" in \"left hand\"). Smoke-check fixed an invalid 2-letter anagram (\"to\"), 10 vocab pools that wrongly included the headword as a distractor, two anagram cues with a stray ___, and circular/leaking defs. Verify: round 1 set strict on 7 meaning-flip/agreement minimal pairs + reworded two \"wall\"-masked defs (gate, rock-climbing); round 2 caught 2 more strict siblings (ec.004/005) — all fixed, then clean. The don't-have-to ≠ mustn't distinction is taught in German explainDe (mustn't is untaught). 6 glosses + 53 translations adjudicated; 2 validator-warns are the benign sentence-initial-blank/lowercase-answer pattern (grader normalizes case). rejectRate 0.0%."
